<topic id="webdav-actions-at-file-level">
  <title>Actions Available at File Level</title><prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords><indexterm>WebDAV Connection<indexterm>actions at file level</indexterm></indexterm></keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>The contextual menu of a file node in a WebDAV connection in the <uicontrol>Data Source
        Explorer</uicontrol> view contains the following actions:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><uicontrol><image href="../img/bt_open_resource.png"/> Open </uicontrol> - Allows you to
        open the selected file in the editor;</li>
      <li><ph conref="webdav-actions-at-folder-level.dita#webdav-actions-at-folder-level/cut_webdav"
        />;</li>
      <li><ph
          conref="webdav-actions-at-folder-level.dita#webdav-actions-at-folder-level/copy_webdav"
        />;</li>
      <li><ph id="copy_location"><uicontrol>Copy Location</uicontrol> - copies an application
          specific URL for the selected resource to the clipboard. You can use this URL for various
          actions like opening or transforming the resources</ph>;</li>
      <li><ph id="rename_file"><uicontrol>Rename</uicontrol> - allows you to change the name of the
          selected file</ph>;</li>
      <li><ph id="delete_file"><uicontrol><image href="../img/RemoveSelected16.gif"/> Delete
          </uicontrol> - removes the selected file</ph>;</li>
      <li><ph id="refresh_file"><uicontrol><image href="../img/bt_refresh.png"/> Refresh
          </uicontrol> - performs a refresh of the selected node</ph>;</li>
      <li><ph id="properties_files"><uicontrol><image href="../img/bt_properties.png"/> Properties
          </uicontrol> - displays the properties of the current file in a dialog</ph>;</li>
      <li><ph
          conref="webdav-actions-at-connection-level.dita#webdav-actions-at-connection-level/find_replace_in_files"
        />.</li>
    </ul>
  </body>
